---
import { withBase } from '../../lib/url';
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { TECHNIQUES } from '../../lib/techniques';
---

<Base
  title="Geomantic Reading Techniques"
  description="The classical techniques for reading a geomantic chart: Judge and Witnesses, modes of perfection, springing of figures, projection of points, dignities and aspects."
>
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ name: 'Techniques' }]} />
  <h1>Reading Techniques</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    Casting the chart is the lesser half of geomancy; the art lies in reading it. As Agrippa says,
    “this whole Art consisteth in the commixtures of the figures, and the natures thereof.” These
    pages set out the classical methods, each grounded in quotations from the sources.
  </p>
  <ul class="technique-list">
    {
      TECHNIQUES.map((t) => (
        <li>
          <a href={withBase(`/techniques/${t.slug}/`)}>{t.title}</a>
          <p>{t.description}</p>
        </li>
      ))
    }
  </ul>
</Base>

<style>
  .lead {
    font-size: var(--text-md);
  }
  .technique-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .technique-list li {
    padding: var(--space-4) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  .technique-list a {
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: var(--text-md);
  }
  .technique-list p {
    margin: var(--space-1) 0 0;
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
  }
</style>
